Annotated Turing
----------------

I wrote this code because I wanted to try out the examples from the book
The Annotated Turing by Charles Petzold.

To use it (in Emacs/Slime), simply C-x C-f ch5.lisp, C-c C-k and do:

; Constructs the example from page 81
CL-USER> (p81)
NEXT

; Step through the program with (next)
CL-USER> (next)
TAPE: 0_  NEXT: C
       ^  STEP: 1
NIL
CL-USER> (next)
TAPE: 0__  NEXT: E
        ^  STEP: 2
NIL
CL-USER> (next)
TAPE: 0_1_  NEXT: F
         ^  STEP: 3
NIL
CL-USER> (next)
TAPE: 0_1__  NEXT: B
          ^  STEP: 4
NIL
CL-USER> (next)
TAPE: 0_1_0_  NEXT: C
           ^  STEP: 5
NIL
CL-USER> 